A '''Sertoli cell'''  is a  cell found in the [[testes]]. Its main function is to help the developing sperm cells through the stages of spermatogenesis - the process of turning [[stem cell]]s into [[sperm]]. It was also called the "mother cell." The cell also helps in the creation of stem cells.


==Name==
Sertoli cells get their name from Enrico Sertoli, an [[Italy|Italian]] [[Physiology|physiologist]]. He discovered them while studying [[medicine]] in the University of Pavia, [[Italy]]. He published a description of this cell in 1865.  As of 2006, two [[textbook]]s have been published that are almost entirely about the Sertoli cell .

